
@startuml

' Define the classes and their attributes

class Game {
  - id: String
  + players: List<Player>
  + deck: Deck
  + scoringTable: ScoringTable
}

class Player {
  - id: String
  + name: String
}

class Deck {
  - id: String
  + cards: List<Card>
  + MAX_CARDS = 48
}

abstract class Card {
  - id: String
  + suit: Suit
  + rank: Rank
  + compare(otherCard): ComparisonResult
}

enum Suit {
  DIAMONDS
  HEARTS
  SPADES
  CLUBS
}

enum Rank {
  SEVEN
  EIGHT
  NINE
  TEN
  JACK
  QUEEN
  KING
  ACE
}

enum ComparisonResult {
  LOWER
  EQUAL
  HIGHER
}

class ScoringTable {
  - id: String
  + rounds: List<Round>
}

abstract class Round {
  - id: String
  + winningPlayers: List<Player>
  + points: Int
}

class JackRound extends Round {}

class SoloRound extends Round {
  + soloType: SoloType
  + soloPlayer: Player
}

class MandatorySoloRound extends SoloRound {}

enum SoloType {
  TRUMP_SOLO
  JACK_SOLO
  QUEEN_SOLO
}

' Relationships

Game "1" -- "4" Player : has
Deck "1" -- "*" Card : contains
ScoringTable "1" -- "*" Round : has
Round "0..*" -- "1" JackRound : can be
Round "0..*" -- "1" SoloRound : can be
SoloRound "1" -- "1" Player : has solo player
SoloRound "1" -- "1" SoloType : has type
MandatorySoloRound "1" -- "1" SoloRound : is a special case of

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Game`** holds all components of the system (players, deck, scoring table).
- **`Deck`** contains a list of `Card`s, limited to 48.
- **`Card`** is abstract with attributes like suit and rank; it has a method for comparison.
- **`Suit` and `Rank`** are enums that define the properties of a card.
- **`ScoringTable`** tracks all rounds.
- **`Round`** is an abstract base class. It has two concrete types:
  - **`JackRound`**: A specific kind of round.
  - **`SoloRound`**: Can have subtypes like **`MandatorySoloRound`**, and includes a solo type and solo player.
- Each object has a unique ID attribute (`id`) as required.

